      "comment_id" : 56142123,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "I used <code>Runnable</code> in this way, and then someone saw this Runnable, and thought &quot;runnable, aha, threads&quot; and edited the code and forked a thread. That resulted in a bug. So nowadays I don&#39;t use <code>Runnable</code> as a callback. Related question (well, answer): <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/a/30183786/694469\">stackoverflow.com/a/30183786/694469</a>"
