      "body" : "@AndrewMcCoist Well, <code>Runnable</code> is the only functional interface in the JDK having a method with no parameters and void return type. You can either use it whenever you need such interface, or you can define your own interface for cases you think the <code>Runnable</code> interface is not appropriate for."
